\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. D. compactum} (Boiss. & Heldr.) J. Holub,{\i  Folia Geobot. Phytotax.} ({\i Praha}){\b  5}: 436 (1970) ({\i Avena compacta} Boiss. & Heldr.). Stems 10-30(-50) cm, erect, slender, glabrous, smooth. Leaves 5-18 cm × 0·5-0·8 mm, setaceous, convolute, rigid, somewhat pungent, glabrous, smooth, with caducous lamina; ligule 1-1·5 mm, shortly ciliate at apex; basal sheaths persistent. Panicle 3-6 cm, with (2-)3-6(-7) spikelets; branches up to 6 mm, erect, usually with 1 spikelet. Spikelets 14-20(-25) mm, with (3-)4-7 (-9) florets, yellowish-green, shining. Glumes lanceolate, acuminate, glabrous, the lower (8-)10-14(-15) mm, the upper (9-)11-15(-17) mm. Lemma 8-14 mm, ovate-lanceolate; awn 11-20 mm. Palea 6-11 mm, linear-lanceolate. Anthers 3-4·5 mm.{\i  Mountain rocks and stony pastures; calcicole. S., W. & C. parts of Balkan peninsula.} Al Bu Gr Ju.
