\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 64.     Arrhenatherum}        Beauv.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By J. Holub. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennials; basal internodes often swollen and globose. Leaves flat, convolute when young, not strongly ribbed above. Inflorescence a panicle. Spikelets slightly compressed laterally, usually with 2 florets and one rudiment. Lower floret male, with a geniculate dorsal awn arising from the lower 1/3 of lemma, the upper female or hermaphrodite, usually with a short, slender, straight seta, rarely both florets hermaphrodite and awned. Glumes unequal, hyaline, the lower 1- to 3-veined, the upper about as long as florets, 3(-5)-veined. Lemma 5- to 9-veined. Palea shorter than lemma, shortly 2-dentate at apex, ciliate on keels. Lodicules 2. Stamens 3. Florets falling together at maturity. Grain more or less terete, with hilum 1/2-2/3 its length.
\par

